title: Field Profiles
description:
Data profiling information about the published fields on the DataSF open data portal

The source code that generates this dataset can be found at: 
https://github.com/DataSF/datasf-profiler

columns.name: columnID
columns.description:
The id for the field. This id also appears in the master data dictionary dictionary dataset at 
https://data.sfgov.org/City-Management-and-Ethics/-alpha-Field-Dictionary-for-Open-Data-Portal-Datas/wn8x-uk7i

columns.name: datasetID
columns.description: The four by four of the dataset that field in

columns.name: Dataset Name
columns.description: The name of the dataset that the field is in

columns.name: Field Name
columns.description: The name of the field

columns.name: Field Type
columns.description: Type of field, either: text, numeric, boolean, timestamp, geometry: point, geometry: line, geometry: polygon, geometry: multiline, geometry: multipolygon

columns.name: Total Count
columns.description: Total number of rows in dataset, used in other derived calculations

columns.name: Null Count
columns.description: count of the number of records with a NULL value

columns.name: Missing Count
columns.description: count of the number of records with a missing value (i.e. non-NULL absence of data e.g. character spaces)

columns.name: Actual Count
columns.description: count of the number of records with an actual value (i.e. non-NULL and non-missing)

columns.name: Cardinality
columns.description: aka the number of distinct values

columns.name: Completeness
columns.description: percentage calculated as Actual divided by the total number of records

columns.name: Distinctness
columns.description: percentage calculated as Cardinality divided by the total number of records

columns.name: Uniqueness
columns.description: percentage calculated as Cardinality divided by Actual

columns.name: Is Primary Key Candidate
columns.description: A boolean field indicating whether the field might be a primary key for the dataset based on its profile. Where uniqueness = 100%

columns.name: Min Field Length
columns.description: The min number of characters/digits in a field

columns.name: Max Field Length
columns.description: The max number of characters/digits in a field

columns.name: Avg Field Length
columns.description: The average number of characters/digits in a field

columns.name: Min Value
columns.description: The mininum value found in a field

columns.name: Max Value
columns.description: The maximum value found in a field

columns.name: Mean
columns.description: The average value found in a field

columns.name: Median
columns.description: The middle value found in a field

columns.name: Mode
columns.description: The most frequently occurring value in a field

columns.name: Range
columns.description: The value between the min and the max

columns.name: Sum
columns.description: The sum of all the values in the field

columns.name: Standard Deviation
columns.description: A measure of how spread out numbers in the field are; a concrete measure of the exact distances from the mean

columns.name: Variance
columns.description: A measure that gives a very general idea of the spread the values in a field. A value of zero means that there is no variation in values; All the numbers in the field set are the same

columns.name: Mean Absolute Deviation
columns.description: Another measure that helps you get a sense of how spread out the values in a field are; Tells you how far, on average, all values in the field are from the middle

columns.name: 5th Percentile
columns.description: a measure that indicates the value below which 5% of values in the field fall

columns.name: 25th Percentile
columns.description: a measure that indicates the value below which 25% of values in the field fall

columns.name: 50th Percentile
columns.description: a measure that indicates the value below which 50% of values in the field fall

columns.name: 75th Percentile
columns.description: a measure that indicates the value below which 75% of values in the field fall

columns.name: 95th Percentile
columns.description: a measure that indicates the value below which 95% of values in the field fall

columns.name: IQR
columns.description: The difference between the first quartile and third quartile of the values in a field. This another way to describe the spread of values within a field

columns.name: Kurtosis
columns.description: A measure to describe the distribution, or skewness, of observed values of the field around the mean

columns.name: Skewness
columns.description: A measure of the degree of asymmetry of the distribution of values in a field. If values in the lower tail of the field are more pronounced than the values in the larger tail of the field, the field will have negative skewness. If the reverse is true, the field will have positive skewness. If the two are equal, the field has zero skewness

columns.name: Last Updt Dt Data
columns.description: The date when the data in the field was last updated

columns.name: Days Since Last Updated
columns.description: The number of days between today and the date when the data in the field was last updated

columns.name: Field Alias
columns.description: The alias name of the field- used for identifying global fields across all datasets

columns.name: Global Field
columns.description: A boolean field to indicate whether this field is mapped on to a global alias and definition. Global aliases and definitions are defined once and propagated to the mapped fields.

columns.name: Department
columns.description: The department that generated the field

columns.name: API Key
columns.description: The name of the field when calling it through the dataset's application programming interface. Learn more at https://dev.socrata.com/docs/endpoints.html

columns.name: nbeID
columns.description: The id of the dataset the field is to use the Socrata 2.1 API

columns.name: Profile Last Updt Dt
columns.description: The date that field was last profiled
